1NT pass pass X pass 2C pass 2H pass pass pass
[BCFlags "1f"]
[RotationNote "Board 3, chOption: E, chBasis: S, basisKind:Declarer, nOption:1, nBasis: 2, nRot: 3, useStandardVul: true"]
[BoardVersionToken "f4f7497daf69562b96f4a1857e5dbc370acc316d4f608e767e3eed522619e4fd"]
[Category "Competitive Bidding"]
[Difficulty "intermediate"]
[SkillPath "competitive_bidding/dont"]
[Student "S"]
{In the balancing seat it is distribution that counts, not point count. With a 6-card Major suit and a singleton you should not let them play 1NT. Youdouble.

Partner makes the relay bid of 2\C.  

You bid your suit, 2\H, and everybody passes. Notice that partner had a decent hand, but could not bid over 1NT in the immediate seat.}

